  "text": "In kubernetes/kubernetes v1.32.0, pod security context field validation occurs across multiple components:\n\n**API Validation Layer (pkg/apis/core/validation/validation.go):**\n- ValidateSecurityContext() validates container-level security context including privileged flag checks against cluster capabilities, capability validation, seccomp profile field validation, and allowPrivilegeEscalation constraints\n- validatePodSpecSecurityContext() validates pod-level security context including seccomp profile enforcement\n- validateSeccompProfileField() validates seccomp profile structure and type\n- ValidateSeccompProfile() validates seccomp profile strings and annotations\n- ValidateSeccompPodAnnotations() validates deprecated seccomp annotations\n- validateSeccompProfileType() validates the seccomp profile type (RuntimeDefault, Localhost, Unconfined)\n\n**Runtime Enforcement Layer (pkg/kubelet/kuberuntime/*):**\n- verifyRunAsNonRoot() in security_context_others.go (Linux) and security_context_windows.go (Windows) enforces runAsNonRoot policy by checking if container is running as root (UID 0 on Linux, ContainerAdministrator on Windows)\n- convertToRuntimeSecurityContext() in security_context.go converts SecurityContext to runtime API, handling privileged flag and other fields\n- convertToRuntimeCapabilities() in security_context.go converts Kubernetes Capabilities to runtime API capabilities\n- determineEffectiveSecurityContext() in security_context.go synthesizes effective security context from pod and container levels\n- getSeccompProfile() in helpers.go resolves seccomp profile from container or pod level with runtime default fallback\n- fieldSeccompProfile() in helpers.go processes seccomp profile field, handling RuntimeDefault and Localhost types\n\n**Container and Capability Helpers:**\n- HasPrivilegedContainer() in pkg/kubelet/container/helpers.go checks if any container in a pod is privileged\n- DetermineEffectiveSecurityContext() in pkg/securitycontext/util.go merges pod and container security context with container taking precedence\n- Capabilities struct in pkg/capabilities/capabilities.go defines AllowPrivileged flag controlling cluster-wide privileged container allowance"
}

